her of Edward the Confessor, herself a Norman. In modern times, it was only in moderate use early in the 20th century but rose sharply in favour in the 1970s and has since remained perennially popular."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Baroness Emma de Gubion was born about 1043, in Saint-Laurent-la-Conche, Loire, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, France, her father, John de Gubion, was 24 and her mother, Unknown, was 23. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Lewis de Laval Lord of Seaton. She died in Seaton Delaval, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Abt 1043–":"umbes 1043–Surnud","1043–Female":"1043–Surnud","1038–1070":"1038–1070","1056–Female":"1056–Surnud","1065–1096":"1065–1096","1020–Male":"1020–Surnud","1022–Female":"1022–Surnud","Abt 1043":"umbes 1043","1038":"1038","Abt 1056":"umbes 1056","1056":"1056","1022":"1022","1065":"1065","before 1043":"1043","1043":"1043","1020":"1020","1096":"1096","1070":"1070","Maigneux-le-Gabion, Saint-Laurent-la-Conche, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, France":"Saint-Laurent-la-Conche, Loire, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, Prantsusmaa",", , Basse-Normandie, France":"Basse-Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Basse-Normandie, France":"Basse-Normandie, Prantsusmaa","France":"Prantsusmaa","Seaton Delaval, Northumberland district, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Seaton Delaval, Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1043–":"noin 1043–Kuollut","1043–Female":"1043–Kuollut","1038–1070":"1038–1070","1056–Female":"1056–Kuollut","1065–1096":"1065–1096","1020–Male":"1020–Kuollut","1022–Female":"1022–Kuollut","Abt 1043":"noin 1043","1038":"1038","Abt 1056":"noin 1056","1056":"1056","1022":"1022","1065":"1065","before 1043":"1043","1043":"1043","1020":"1020","1096":"1096","1070":"1070","Maigneux-le-Gabion, Saint-Laurent-la-Conche, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, France":"Saint-Laurent-la-Conche, Loire, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, Ranska",", , Basse-Normandie, France":"Basse-Normandie, Ranska","Basse-Normandie, France":"Basse-Normandie, Ranska","Fran